        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 12:48PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1248 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Needmore, or 10 miles northeast of Haleyville, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Moulton, Trinity, Town Creek, Courtland, North Courtland, Hillsboro,
Mt Hope, Chalybeate Springs, Ne Smith, and Caddo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
